Multinational tyre manufacturer subsidiary Goodyear South Africa has appointed Richard Fourie as MD, effective from this month. He succeeds Piotr Czyzyk, who led the company for two years. Fourie has more than 25 years of management and leadership experience from various industries across the globe. He returns to South Africa from Singapore, where he was the Goodyear Asia Pacific marketing director. “I am very excited to be back home in South Africa to take up this new challenge. Goodyear has been an active contributor to the development of South Africa’s mobility sector for over seven decades. “I look forward to building on our successful legacy to continue delivering on our promises to customers, consumers and stakeholders while playing an active role in enabling a seamless, smooth and safe mobility experience today and into the future,” says Fourie.